Members of the Lions Clubs International, District 404B2 Nigeria, have donated backpacks to students of Sango Junior Secondary School, Agege, Lagos State, to mark the 2022 Childrenâ€™s Day. Speaking at the event, which took place on the premises of the school, Lion Kayode Oshunuga, governor of the district, said the objective was to raise awareness about the needs of the deaf students, empathize with them and feel what they feel every day of their lives He added that the event was also organized to remind members of the public that the students were important to society. -Advertisement- He urged Nigerians not to discriminate against disabled people, adding that they should be given adequate education and care so that they can contribute their quota to the development of the country. Also speaking at the event, the chairperson of the organizing committee for the event, Lion Ebun Aina, stressed the importance of educating and empowering disabled people in the community. According to her, the disabled can contribute to the development of the country if they get adequate education and training if they are afforded the opportunity like others. She praised the teachers for their dedication to raising people she said will be great in the future. The students gave different performances using sign language.